*Researchers at Carnegie Mellon have developed a *thin, flexible, skin-mounted haptic device* that provides realistic tactile feedback.*
- The device uses a single actuator to deliver multi-directional sensations, enabling its use in *VR, daily tasks, and object detection*.
- This *imperceptible technology* aims to enhance *sensing, communication, and human-machine interaction* without distractions or cognitive load.

